events.param: terminal LOG 31.11: I like the trees. They’re odd. Still, the last time I saw a tree my parents were still together. After this mission, I’ll go home and see the trees, I think.

note Remember when we used to climb the trees behind my house? We brought along pages and drew plans for a tree house and hid them in the hollows. I went back last year, and I found some of our old drawings. When I picked them up, they fell apart like flakes of ash.

note I’m not so sure about Sam anymore. I keep glancing at them when I think they’re not looking. How do I describe what I’m seeing... There’s a web of darkness slowly splintering over their face. Not a real web, I don’t think. But maybe?
party The sun feels nice here...
party Did you forget we’re still on a ship?
terminal LOG 15.13: Dense irregularities. Hector suggested invasive species? Skeptical. This is a small ship built only last year.
Your party has to strip off their spacesuits and shove them in a backpack. The air is thick with moisture.

This forest is less forest and more like what an astronaut who hasn’t seen a tree for decades might dream up – a caricature of forest. The ground is a tangle of giant roots. Verdant leaves blend together like a bad photoshop brush, amidst fuzzy, twisted trunks.
note Edison died. The new guy is better. I feel guilty about thinking it but it’s true.
note This page has a mediocre pencil drawing of a person’s face with unsettling splinters of darkness scribbled through it.
terminal LOG 46.20: Hector wandered out into the forest last week and we have not seen him since.
